  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hip or knee is a validated treatment of end-stage osteoarthritis, and these interventions
      commonly make a significant improvement in the quality of life of patients. Infection can
      occur in 1-5% of cases. Diagnosis is often difficult, but the knowledge of infected or not
      infected character directly influences the surgical conduct. It is therefore recommended that
      the positive or negative diagnosis is made in the most reliable way possible, but no single
      element only allows a low diagnosis. The concomitant use of several clinical, radiological
      and aggregated into a composite score history could help facilitate this preoperative
      approach during reoperation on prosthetic joint
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
